add a from_iri classmethod to URLObject

add a from_iri classmethod to URLObject

This method parses an address as commonly entered by the user,
converting unicode hostnames to IDNA, encoding the unicode characters
to a URI-compatible format using the IRI rules (mostly), and
also avoiding double-encoding any URL-quoted characters in the input.

Merge pull request #20 from agriffis/querystring-int-values

Allow QueryString.add_param() to work with int values.
Move integer check into qs_encode()

Allow QueryString.add_param() to work with int values.

This seems to happen to me all the time, where higher level code assigns
integer values and then we get a traceback.  Seems harmless to handle
integer querystring values.

This will allow me to avoid the following hack in my code:

    # HACK since URLObject doesn't like ints in query values.
    data = {k: str(v) if isinstance(v, int) else v
            for k, v in data.items()}
    url = url.set_query_params(**data)
Fix a comment.
